Advanced Voice Butler: Google Ecosystem Integration Guide (Omni-Update)

This guide details the technical configuration required to bridge the Advanced Voice Butler with Google Workspace and Google Cloud. By combining a Serverless Apps Script with the Google Maps Platform, the Butler achieves real-time synchronization for calendar events, priority email routing, and proactive travel intelligence—including traffic-aware departure alerts and gas price scouting.

---

Phase 1: Hubitat Cloud Endpoint Preparation
Before configuring external scripts, Hubitat must be authorized to receive secure inbound webhooks.

1. Navigate to Apps Code in Hubitat and select the Advanced Voice Butler application.
2. Select Enable OAuth in App. (No redirect URIs are required).
3. Click Update.
4. Open the Advanced Voice Butler app instance. Navigate to the Live System Dashboard to retrieve your Cloud Webhook URL. Copy the base URL (e.g., everything before /email or /calendar) for use in Phase 3.

---

Phase 2: Google Maps Platform & Travel Intelligence (New)
The Butler uses Google’s professional mapping tools to calculate drive times and find fuel. Note: Google requires a billing account (credit card) to activate these APIs, but provides a $200 monthly credit which covers all Butler activity for free.

1. Create a Project: Go to the Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/) and create a project named "Butler Intelligence."
2. Enable Billing: Go to Billing and link a payment method. This activates the $200/mo free credit.
3. Enable APIs: Navigate to APIs & Services > Library and search for and Enable the following:
    * Distance Matrix API (Calculates traffic-aware drive times).
    * Places API (Finds the cheapest gas stations).
4. Generate Credentials: Go to APIs & Services > Credentials. Click + Create Credentials > API Key. Copy this key.
5. Configure Hubitat:
    * In the Voice Butler app, expand Calendar & Appointment Reminders.
    * Paste your API Key.
    * Enter your Home Address (Format: 2530 Williams Rd, Wetumpka, AL 36092).
    * Set a Monthly API Call Limit (e.g., 500) as a hard failsafe to ensure you never exceed the free tier.

---

Phase 3: Google Apps Script Deployment
This script securely pushes verified events from your Gmail and Calendar directly to the Hubitat TTS queue.

1. Access script.google.com and initialize a New Project.
2. Inject the following payload, replacing YOUR_SECURE_HUBITAT_CLOUD_URL_HERE with your URL from Phase 1.

// --- ADVANCED VOICE BUTLER MASTER BRIDGE ---
const HUBITAT_BASE_URL = "YOUR_SECURE_HUBITAT_CLOUD_URL_HERE"; 

function checkImportantEmails() {
  const threads = GmailApp.search('is:unread is:important', 0, 1);
  if (threads.length > 0) {
    const message = threads[0].getMessages()[0];
    const payload = {
      sender: message.getFrom(),
      subject: message.getSubject(),
      snippet: message.getPlainBody().substring(0, 150) + "..."
    };
    UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/email?"), {
      method: 'post', contentType: 'application/json', payload: JSON.stringify(payload)
    });
    message.markRead(); 
  }
  checkOomaVoicemails();
  checkDeliveryEmails();
  pushCalendarUpdates();
}

function checkOomaVoicemails() {
  const threads = GmailApp.search('is:unread from:notify@ooma.com subject:"New Voicemail"', 0, 1);
  if (threads.length > 0) {
    const message = threads[0].getMessages()[0];
    const subject = message.getSubject();
    const body = message.getPlainBody();
    const caller = subject.replace("New Voicemail from", "").trim();
    let transcription = "No transcription available.";
    if (body.includes("Message:")) {
      transcription = body.split("Message:")[1].split("To listen to")[0].trim();
    }
    const payload = { isVoicemail: true, sender: caller, msgContent: transcription };
    UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/email?"), {
      method: 'post', contentType: 'application/json', payload: JSON.stringify(payload)
    });
    message.markRead(); 
  }
}

function checkDeliveryEmails() {
  const threads = GmailApp.search('is:unread (subject:"out for delivery" OR subject:"package arriving" OR subject:"scheduled for delivery")', 0, 1);
  if (threads.length > 0) {
    const message = threads[0].getMessages()[0];
    const payload = { isDelivery: true, sender: message.getFrom(), subject: message.getSubject() };
    UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/email?"), {
      method: 'post', contentType: 'application/json', payload: JSON.stringify(payload)
    });
    message.markRead(); 
  }
}

function pushCalendarUpdates() {
  const now = new Date();
  const events = CalendarApp.getDefaultCalendar().getEvents(now, new Date(now.getTime() + (5 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)));
  let upcoming = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < events.length; i++) {
    let evt = events[i];
    if (evt.isAllDayEvent()) continue;
    let startTime = evt.getStartTime().getTime();
    if (startTime <= now.getTime()) continue;
    upcoming.push({ title: evt.getTitle(), epoch: startTime, location: evt.getLocation() });
    if (upcoming.length >= 5) break;
  }
  UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/calendar?"), {
    method: 'post', contentType: 'application/json', payload: JSON.stringify({ events: upcoming })
  });
}

