Phase 4: Setting the Automation Trigger
To keep the Butler updated without manual refreshing:

1. In the Apps Script editor, click the Triggers (Clock Icon) in the left sidebar.
2. Click + Add Trigger.
3. Set "Choose which function to run" to checkImportantEmails.
4. Set "Select event source" to Time-driven.
5. Set "Select type of time based trigger" to Minutes timer.
6. Set "Select minute interval" to Every 5 minutes.
7. Click Save and authorize the script when prompted.

---

Phase 5: Verification and Testing
The Butler includes built-in diagnostic tools to ensure your integration is successful.

* Google API Test: Click the ▶️ Test Google API Connection button in the Hubitat UI. The Butler should speak your current drive time to a local destination and send a push notification to your phone with a clickable Google Maps navigation link for the cheapest gas.
* Calendar Sync: Add an event to your Google Calendar with a specific address in the Location field. Click 🔄 Force Sync Calendar in Hubitat. The Butler should now show that event as his "Next Destination."
* Quick Exit Test: Put your house into Away Mode. Open an exit door. The Butler should bid you farewell and immediately push the drive-time/gas intel for your next calendar event to your mobile device.

