Calendar Event Creation via Voice Butler
Create the Google Apps Script Webhook
Because Hubitat handles Google OAuth authentication poorly on its own, the safest and most reliable way to write an event to your calendar is to use a simple Google Apps Script as a bridge.

Go to script.google.com.

Click New Project.

Delete the default code and paste this in:

JavaScript
function doPost(e) {
  try {
    var data = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
    var title = data.title;
    var dateStr = data.date; // YYYY-MM-DD
    var timeStr = data.time; // HH:mm
    var durationMins = parseInt(data.duration) || 60;
    
    // Construct Date objects
    var startTime = new Date(dateStr + "T" + timeStr + ":00");
    var endTime = new Date(startTime.getTime() + (durationMins * 60000));
    
    // Write to your primary calendar
    var calendar = CalendarApp.getDefaultCalendar();
    calendar.createEvent(title, startTime, endTime);
    
    return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({"status": "success"})).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
  } catch (error) {
    return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({"status": "error", "message": error.toString()})).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
  }
}
Click Deploy -> New deployment in the top right.

Choose Web app as the type.

Set "Execute as" to Me.

Set "Who has access" to Anyone. (Hubitat needs to be able to reach it).

Click Deploy, authorize your account, and copy the Web app URL.

Paste that URL into the new Google Apps Script Webhook URL field inside your Voice Butler Calendar settings in Hubitat.
